## Part 2: Implementation Plan for Content Syndication Feature

### Feature Overview
Automatically syndicate published blog posts to an external content aggregator API (`https://api.content-aggregator.com/v1/posts`) via HTTP POST upon successful publication.

### Step-by-Step Implementation Plan

#### Step 1: Define the New Port (Interface)

**New File**: `src/Domain/Ports/IContentSyndicator.cs` (or add to existing ports module)

```csharp
namespace TempoScribePro.Domain.Ports
{
    /// <summary>
    /// Outbound port for syndicating published content to external aggregators.
    /// </summary>
    public interface IContentSyndicator
    {
        /// <summary>
        /// Syndicates a published post to an external content aggregator.
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="post">The published post to syndicate.</param>
        /// <param name="cancellationToken">Cancellation token.</param>
        /// <returns>Result indicating success or failure of syndication.</returns>
        Task<SyndicationResult> SyndicateAsync(
            Post post,
            CancellationToken cancellationToken = default);
    }

    public sealed record SyndicationResult(
        bool IsSuccess,
        string? ExternalId,
        string? ErrorMessage);
}
```

**Purpose**: This interface belongs in the Domain/Application layer and defines the contract for content syndication without any knowledge of HTTP, REST, or specific external APIs.

**Location in Hexagon**: Outbound Port (driven port)

#### Step 2: Create the Secondary Adapter (HTTP Client Implementation)

**New File**: `src/Infrastructure/Syndication/ContentAggregatorSyndicatorAdapter.cs`

```csharp
namespace TempoScribePro.Infrastructure.Syndication
{
    /// <summary>
    /// HTTP adapter that syndicates posts to the external content aggregator API.
    /// Implements the <see cref="IContentSyndicator"/> port.
    /// </summary>
    public sealed class ContentAggregatorSyndicatorAdapter : IContentSyndicator
    {
        private readonly HttpClient _httpClient;
        private readonly ContentSyndicationOptions _options;
        private readonly ILogger<ContentAggregatorSyndicatorAdapter> _logger;
        private readonly AsyncRetryPolicy<HttpResponseMessage> _retryPolicy;

        public ContentAggregatorSyndicatorAdapter(
            HttpClient httpClient,
            IOptions<ContentSyndicationOptions> options,
            ILogger<ContentAggregatorSyndicatorAdapter> logger)
        {
            _httpClient = httpClient ?? throw new ArgumentNullException(nameof(httpClient));
            _options = options?.Value ?? throw new ArgumentNullException(nameof(options));
            _logger = logger ?? throw new ArgumentNullException(nameof(logger));

            // Configure Polly retry for transient HTTP failures
            _retryPolicy = Policy<HttpResponseMessage>
                .Handle<HttpRequestException>()
                .OrResult(r => r.StatusCode >= HttpStatusCode.InternalServerError)
                .WaitAndRetryAsync(
                    retryCount: 3,
                    sleepDurationProvider: attempt => TimeSpan.FromSeconds(Math.Pow(2, attempt)));
        }

        public async Task<SyndicationResult> SyndicateAsync(
            Post post,
            CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)
        {
            var payload = new
            {
                title = post.Title,
                slug = post.Slug,
                content = post.MarkdownBody,
                publishedAt = post.PublishedAtUtc,
                author = post.AuthorName,
                isPremium = post.IsPremium
            };

            var json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(payload);
            var content = new StringContent(json, Encoding.UTF8, "application/json");

            _httpClient.DefaultRequestHeaders.Authorization =
                new AuthenticationHeaderValue("Bearer", _options.ApiKey);

            try
            {
                var response = await _retryPolicy.ExecuteAsync(async ct =>
                    await _httpClient.PostAsync(_options.EndpointUrl, content, ct),
                    cancellationToken);

                if (response.IsSuccessStatusCode)
                {
                    var responseBody = await response.Content.ReadAsStringAsync(cancellationToken);
                    var result = JsonSerializer.Deserialize<SyndicationApiResponse>(responseBody);

                    _logger.LogInformation(
                        "Post {PostId} syndicated successfully. ExternalId: {ExternalId}",
                        post.Id, result?.Id);

                    return new SyndicationResult(true, result?.Id, null);
                }

                var error = await response.Content.ReadAsStringAsync(cancellationToken);
                _logger.LogWarning(
                    "Syndication failed for Post {PostId}. Status: {StatusCode}, Error: {Error}",
                    post.Id, response.StatusCode, error);

                return new SyndicationResult(false, null, error);
            }
            catch (Exception ex)
            {
                _logger.LogError(ex, "Syndication exception for Post {PostId}", post.Id);
                return new SyndicationResult(false, null, ex.Message);
            }
        }

        private sealed record SyndicationApiResponse(string? Id);
    }
}
```

**Purpose**: Concrete implementation that handles all HTTP-specific concerns (HttpClient, JSON serialization, retry policies, authentication headers).

**Location in Hexagon**: Secondary Adapter (driven adapter) - sits outside the hexagon, implements the port

